"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-world-2024-0927-1472283-paris-olympics-eiffel-tower\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Workers in Paris have removed the Olympics logo from the Eiffel Tower, returning the beloved monument to its usual form - but perhaps only temporarily.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983829184, \"rank\": 1.6171344771300424e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo has promised to build new Olympic rings and return them to the landmark as a tribute to the hugely successful Olympic Games held over the summer.\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 165, \"end\": 177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The proposition has been criticised by descendants of the tower's designer Gustave Eiffel, as well as conservation groups and many Parisians.\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustave Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After initially suggesting the rings should be permanent, Ms Hidalgo has proposed they remain on the city's best-known symbol until the next Olympics in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999998917676353, \"rank\": 1.0823243702717846e-07, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999951785917162, \"rank\": 4.510326605198688e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Workers using a crane removed the 30-tonne rings from between the first and second floors of the tower overnight, just under four months after they were put up on 7 June.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new rings, which the International Olympic Committee is expected to pay for, would be lighter versions and less prominent, according to a deputy Paris mayor, Pierre Rabadan.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983829184, \"rank\": 1.6171344771300424e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre Rabadan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Culture Minister Rachida Dati, a longtime critic and opponent of Ms Hidalgo, has cast doubt over the idea, saying the Socialist city leader would need to respect procedures protecting historic buildings.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachida Dati\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\"}, {\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999998917676353, \"rank\": 1.0823243702717846e-07, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Hidalgo also wants to retain the innovative cauldron placed in front of the Louvre museum as well as statues of illustrious women used during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999998917676353, \"rank\": 1.0823243702717846e-07, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidal